Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.28,0:00:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to Essential Hayek \N 欢迎来到哈耶克简要
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.72,0:00:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Don Boudreaux \N 我是Don Boudreaux
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.22,0:00:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,professor of economics at George Mason University \N 乔治梅森大学经济学教授
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.00,0:00:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,senior fellow with the Fraser Institute \N 弗雷泽研究所高级研究员
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.20,0:00:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and blogger at Café Hayek \N 博客Café Hayek的博主之一
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.38,0:00:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This video was part of the Fraser Institute initiative \N 本视频是由弗雷泽研究所制作的
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.22,0:00:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to present the key ideas of F.A. Hayek in an easily accessible format \N 对哈耶克关键思想的通俗介绍
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.58,0:00:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Hayek observed that the challenge of living in a modern society involves \N 哈耶克观察到在现代社会生活的挑战包含
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.12,0:00:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,two sets of very different interactions \N 两套非常不同的互动方式
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.26,0:00:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,those that occur among our family and friends \N 一种是与家庭和朋友打交道的方式
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.94,0:00:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and those that occur in the external world \N 另一种是与外部世界打交道的方式
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.30,0:00:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's simplify this rather complex idea with an example \N 让我们举例来说明这个复杂的想法
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.00,0:00:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Tom \N 这是Tom
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.70,0:00:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He owns a bicycle repair shop \N 他经营着一家自行车维修店
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.42,0:00:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Tom repairs people's bikes \N Tom修理顾客的自行车
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.06,0:00:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and in return, his customers pay him \N 顾客则付给Tom钱作为回报
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.06,0:00:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Tom is also married and a father \N Tom也结婚了并已为人父
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.00,0:00:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,When Tom is at home with his family \N Tom与家人在一块时
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.12,0:00:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the interactions between his wife and children \N 一家人之间的互动
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.58,0:01:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,are very different from those in Tom's bike shop \N 与Tom自行车店里的互动非常不同
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.16,0:01:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, if Tom's son needs his bike repaired \N 举个栗子，如果Tom的儿子自行车坏了
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.12,0:01:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,he simply asks Tom \N 他只需要跟Tom说一声就行了
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.98,0:01:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't expect Tom to charge his son for the repair as he would a customer in store \N 我们并不认为Tom会像对顾客那样对儿子收费
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.12,0:01:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Hayek observed that a family is not a market \N 哈耶克观察到家庭与市场不一样
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.80,0:01:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and the rules of the market do not apply to the family \N 市场上的规则也不适用于家庭
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.86,0:01:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,As a father \N 作为一个父亲
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.24,0:01:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Tom gains satisfaction from helping his son by repairing his bike \N Tom从帮助他儿子修车中获得了满足
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.08,0:01:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,This satisfaction is different from the feelings he experiences with his customers \N 这种满足与他从顾客那所获得的感受不同
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.72,0:01:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost all of them Tom doesn't know outside the work \N 几乎所有顾客Tom在工作外都不认识
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.26,0:01:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Likewise, Hayek explained that society at large cannot operate like a family \N 类似的，哈耶克描述了大型社会是无法像个家庭那样运转的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.96,0:01:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If Tom treated his customers like his son \N 如果Tom像对待孩子那样对待顾客
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.24,0:01:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and didn't charge them for fixing their bikes \N 为他们免费修理自行车
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.86,0:01:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,his business would soon go broke \N 他的生意很快就会难以为继
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.80,0:01:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Hayek's point is that markets and economies would collapse \N 哈耶克认为如果我们试图让社会像个扩展大家庭那样运行
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.78,0:01:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,if we try to operate society at large as if it were one big extended family \N 市场和经济将会崩溃
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.94,0:02:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Hayek identified a subtle, but key aspect of a society \N 哈耶克指出了一个社会微妙又关键的一面
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.08,0:02:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,which is that we're governed by two distinct sets of rules and constraints \N 即有两套不同的规则和约束作用于我们的行为
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.54,0:02:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,both function well within their own spheres \N 在它们各自的范围内都运行良好
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.28,0:02:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but great disruptions and costs occur when we try to transplant one set of rules to the other sphere \N 但当我们把其中之一用于另一个的范围时，就会导致严重的破坏
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.54,0:02:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,To learn more and to download <Essential Hayek> for free \N 想要下载和更多了解《哈耶克简要》
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.58,0:02:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,visit www.essentialhayek.org \N 请访问www.essentialhayek.org
